---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MigrateBody from '../../components/MigrateBody.astro';
---
<Layout seoSlug="/migrate/from-slicewp">
  <MigrateBody
    sourceName="SliceWP"
    sourceUrl="https://slicewp.com"
    intro="Switching from SliceWP to Asteris Affiliates takes about 15 minutes and preserves your affiliates, commissions, and payout history. Both plugins run self-hosted, so the migration is purely a data transfer."
    exportSteps={[
      { name: 'Export from SliceWP', text: 'In WordPress admin, open SliceWP → Affiliates and export affiliates and commissions to CSV.' },
    ]}
    caveats={[
      'SliceWP Pro\'s coupon-tracking is handled by Asteris Affiliates\' built-in coupon attribution — re-link coupons to affiliates after import.',
      'If you used SliceWP add-ons (e.g. recurring commissions), the recurring schedule needs to be re-set in Asteris Affiliates Pro.',
    ]}
    vsSlug="/slicewp-vs-asteris"
  >
    <section class="prose">
      <div class="prose-inner">
        <h2>What the SliceWP-to-Asteris migration actually does</h2>
        <p>SliceWP stores affiliate data in standard WordPress tables and exports it as a clean CSV — which makes this one of the easiest migrations in the WordPress affiliate ecosystem. The WP-CLI command <code>wp asteris-aff import --source=slicewp --csv=/path/to/slicewp-export.csv</code> reads the CSV and maps it to Asteris's tables. Specifically:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Affiliates:</strong> WP user ID (preserved as the same WP user → same Asteris affiliate ID), email, name, payout-method preference, default commission rate, status (active / pending / rejected), date of registration. All preserved.</li>
          <li><strong>Commissions (called "referrals" in SliceWP):</strong> affiliate ID, related order ID, amount, currency, status (pending / paid / refunded), date. Status maps directly to Asteris's pending / unpaid / paid / rejected states.</li>
          <li><strong>Coupon attributions:</strong> SliceWP Pro tracks coupons-as-affiliate-links. Asteris re-creates the coupon → affiliate mapping after import — verify each coupon code links to the correct affiliate in Settings → Coupons.</li>
          <li><strong>Visit history:</strong> SliceWP doesn't expose visit-level data via its standard export, so visit history isn't preserved row-by-row. Aggregate visit counts per affiliate are estimated from referral history.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>The recommended sequence</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Install Asteris alongside SliceWP</strong> — they don't conflict.</li>
          <li><strong>Export from SliceWP</strong> via Affiliates → Tools → Export.</li>
          <li><strong>Import to Asteris</strong> via WP-CLI: <code>wp asteris-aff import --source=slicewp --csv=...</code>.</li>
          <li><strong>Spot-check 5–10 affiliates</strong> in Asteris admin — balances should match SliceWP exactly.</li>
          <li><strong>Switch tracking</strong>: deactivate SliceWP's tracking (Settings → Tracking → Disabled), leaving the plugin installed for 30 days.</li>
          <li><strong>Email affiliates their new dashboard URL.</strong> Asteris's vanity URLs are <code>{`/go/{handle}`}</code> — encourage affiliates to update their links, but existing SliceWP-style links keep working via the compatibility redirect.</li>
          <li><strong>After 30 days clean</strong>, deactivate and delete SliceWP, drop its tables.</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What you gain on day one</h2>
        <p>The features Asteris ships that SliceWP doesn't, available immediately after import: two-tier (MLM) referrals (<a href="/docs/commissions/two-tier">how it works</a>), AI swipe-copy generator (<a href="/docs/growth/ai-swipe-copy">how it works</a>), Stripe Connect Express direct payouts (<a href="/docs/payouts/stripe-connect">how it works</a>), PayPal Payouts API batch payouts (<a href="/docs/payouts/paypal-api">how it works</a>), EDD + Surecart adapters (<a href="/docs/integrations/edd">EDD</a>, <a href="/docs/integrations/surecart">Surecart</a>), cloud-assist fraud detection (<a href="/docs/fraud/cloud-assist">how it works</a>), A/B email testing (<a href="/docs/growth/ab-email-testing">how it works</a>). <a href="/slicewp-vs-asteris">SliceWP vs Asteris full comparison →</a></p>

        <p><strong>Stuck or want us to run it?</strong> Pro + Agency licences include migration assistance — email <a href="mailto:support@asterisaffiliates.com">support@asterisaffiliates.com</a> with your licence key.</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </MigrateBody>
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose { padding: 64px 24px; background: #fff; border-top: 1px solid var(--c-border); }
  .prose-inner { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .prose h2 { font-size: clamp(22px, 3vw, 28px); margin: 32px 0 16px; }
  .prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .prose p { font-size: 15.5px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--c-text); margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .prose ul, .prose ol { padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 14px; }
  .prose li { padding: 5px 0; line-height: 1.6; font-size: 15px; }
  .prose a { color: var(--c-mint); font-weight: 600; }
  .prose code { background: rgba(0,0,0,0.06); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12.5px; }
  .prose strong { color: var(--c-text); font-weight: 700; }
</style>
